# E-Commerce Dashboard

## Overview

This project is an interactive E-Commerce Dashboard designed to visualize and manage sales, orders, and customer data. It features charts, tables, and filters for easy navigation and analysis.

## Live Demo

A live version of the dashboard is hosted here: [Your Live Demo Link](https://your-demo-link.com)

## Features

- Visualize sales, orders, and customer metrics
- Interactive charts and tables
- Sample data included for demonstration

## Setup Instructions

1. **Clone the Repository**

    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/Rakesh539704e/ecommerce-dashboard.git
    cd ecommerce-dashboard
    ```

2. **Install Dependencies**

    ```bash
    npm install
    ```

3. **Run the Dashboard Locally**

    ```bash
    npm start
    ```

    The dashboard will be available at `http://localhost:3000`.

## Dependencies

- React
- Chart.js (or your chosen charting library)
- [List any other dependencies here]

## Navigating the Dashboard

- **Dashboard Home:** View key metrics and charts.
- **Orders:** Browse and filter order data.
- **Customers:** Analyze customer information.
- **Products:** Review product performance.

Use the sidebar or navigation menu to switch between sections.

## Sample Data

The dashboard is pre-populated with sample data for demonstration purposes. You can modify or replace this data in the `/data` directory.

